A couple hundred plays by inexperienced players while we've had it (so games didn't last long), kept in a smoke-free house, regular professional cleaning/waxing/maintenance/etc (hasn't been played since last service, so everything is working). title: Creality Ender 3 V3 SE with Upgrades
decription:
I got this Ender 3 V3 SE as a gift not too long ago to see if I like 3d printing, since it’s a great beginner 3d printer that have auto bed leveling. I’ve only used it for a couple of months but I love the quality it’s able to produce and how easy it is to set up and just print. Since then I’ve added a few upgrades to it:

New PEI textured magnetic plate for better bed adhesion

Upgraded the X-Axis to Creality’s official Linear rail for better stability and more reliable results 

Upgraded the hot end fan to a noctua for more efficient heat distribution and quieter operation because the stock fan was abnormally loud.

Upgraded the 4010 filament blower to a 5015 one for better cooling and better overhang results 

Added the gantry support braces for less vibrations and VFAs.

This little guy prints like a champ and will be an amazing machine for anyone who likes to tinker or just wants a plug and play 3D machine. 

I’ve upgraded to a Bambu Lab printer since then so I find myself not using this anymore, so I’m hoping to find a home for it. Hit me up if you have any questions. Comes with original box and packaging. I am willing to disassemble it and pack it in its box but I have the gantry pretty close to perfectly perpendicular to the bed so I’m leaving it as is for the next owner unless specifically requested.

title: Powered Subwoofer Monoprice
decription:
This is an 8" powered subwoofer capable of producing 60 watts (RMS) output. 
Working, no returns. 
No trades.
The subwoofer has a frequency response range of 50 to 250 Hz with a lowpass crossover filter, which can be adjusted from 50 to 150 Hz. Gain and frequency knobs on the control panel allow you to adjust the crossover filter and the power output for the optimum blend and balance of bass output with your stereo or surround speakers.Waterproof : No
The subwoofer has multiple input options, which allow it to be used with any existing stereo or 5.1 (or greater) amplifier system. For each input there is a corresponding output.
High-level inputs accept a full-range signal from the amplifier's stereo speaker outputs. When connecting the unit as part of a 5.1 system, these would be taken off the Front Left and Front Right outputs in parallel to the standard pair of front speakers. The subwoofer provides its own power and includes impedance matching circuitry, so this will not reduce the power output to the front speakers or affect the overall impedance load on the amplifier.
Additionally, the subwoofer has a set of right/left Line Level inputs. If using a standard stereo system, without a special subwoofer output, you can connect these to the left and right line level outputs on the amp. The subwoofer will then combine the signals to process the mono bass signal it needs to drive the speaker. If you are using an amplifier with a single mono subwoofer line level output, simply use an RCA "Y" cable to split the output and send it to the two line level inputs on the subwoofer.
The subwoofer is housed in an attractive black wood cabinet that measures 13.75" x 11.75" x 11.75" (H x W x D). The driver and a 2 3/4" sound port are located on the front, covered by a black cloth speaker grill.

decription:
JANUARY 1ST! Room opening up for Rent in the heart of Logan Square

HELLO EVERYONE!! 🙂

We are looking for 1 new roommate starting JANUARY 1st! 🏡

I should say I’m prioritizing WOMEN bc I want my femme roomie to have another girlie around instead of 2 dudes… hope you understand… 

At such a prime location, right in front of Palmer Square park, in the heart of Logan Square!

🚇 Only a 5-minute walk from the Blue Line (California Station).
💰 Affordable at $750 per month (your part)
🧺 Laundry in unit (complimentary), utilities not included.

I'd say we’re easy going and don't ask for much, but some basic points we’re looking for in a roommate are:

🌟 Kind-hearted / friendly enough
🧹 Clean, without being a clean freak
🤝 Willing to contribute and help out
🌿 Health-conscious (ishhh)
💼 Financially responsible
🔐 Honest and trustworthy
🎨 Creative spirits are a plus!

and good vibes only!

If this sounds like a good living situation for you, pls reach out and message me! Hoping to create a welcoming space! 🏡

About me: I’m pretty chill and also energetic when the time is right, I work in vintage, schedule is a little flexible, I also love being outside so I try to get out as much as I can specially during the summer. I love dinner parties, although I barely even do them I would like to host a. bit more, sometimes I have some ppl over sometimes during the weekend before going out, I’m not really a house parties person but I like gatherings w a few ppl, these are things we can talk about of course. I consider myself a respectful person I’m not into drama and I’m all for assertive and considerate communication instead of leaving things unsaid when it could cause some passive aggressive buildup. I’m down to be friends w my roommates and hopefully we vibe, I also like my alone times and can def read a room when ppl need their space.

My roommate Gisela is a chef and manager at a fine dining restaurant in River North. She travels frequently, is super chill, and very friendly. Though she tends to keep to herself, she always says hi and engages in conversation when it feels natural. She’s a fantastic cook, works a lot, and is 420-friendly. Overall, she’s easygoing and great to live with.

Please tell me about yourself I would love to hear it and also send me your IG (or w/e social media you may have) I’m a v visual person!

title: Powered Subwoofer Monoprice
decription:
This is an 8" powered subwoofer capable of producing 60 watts (RMS) output. 
Working, no returns. 
No trades.
The subwoofer has a frequency response range of 50 to 250 Hz with a lowpass crossover filter, which can be adjusted from 50 to 150 Hz. Gain and frequency knobs on the control panel allow you to adjust the crossover filter and the power output for the optimum blend and balance of bass output with your stereo or surround speakers.Waterproof : No
The subwoofer has multiple input options, which allow it to be used with any existing stereo or 5.1 (or greater) amplifier system. For each input there is a corresponding output.
High-level inputs accept a full-range signal from the amplifier's stereo speaker outputs. When connecting the unit as part of a 5.1 system, these would be taken off the Front Left and Front Right outputs in parallel to the standard pair of front speakers. The subwoofer provides its own power and includes impedance matching circuitry, so this will not reduce the power output to the front speakers or affect the overall impedance load on the amplifier.
Additionally, the subwoofer has a set of right/left Line Level inputs. If using a standard stereo system, without a special subwoofer output, you can connect these to the left and right line level outputs on the amp. The subwoofer will then combine the signals to process the mono bass signal it needs to drive the speaker. If you are using an amplifier with a single mono subwoofer line level output, simply use an RCA "Y" cable to split the output and send it to the two line level inputs on the subwoofer.
The subwoofer is housed in an attractive black wood cabinet that measures 13.75" x 11.75" x 11.75" (H x W x D). The driver and a 2 3/4" sound port are located on the front, covered by a black cloth speaker grill.

title: RGB Gaming PC | Ryzen 5 5600gt | 32Gb ddr4 Ram | 1tb M.2 ssd | Windows 11 Included
decription:
This is a custom-built gaming PC with Windows 11 installed and activated. This PC has 3 aRGB (Addressable RGB) case fans and 2 sticks of aRGB RAM. The aspects of this PC include:

CPU: Ryzen 5 5600gt
CPU Cooler: Ryzen Stealth Cooler
Motherboard: Gigabyte B550M DS3H AC
RAM: PNY XLR8 Gaming 32 GB
SSD: 
GPU: Ryzen Integrated Graphics 
Case: Okinos Aqua 5
Case Fans: 3x Okinos Aqua Case Fan
PSU: Corsair CX 750w (2023)

CPU:
I chose to go with this CPU because it comes with Ryzen's integrated graphics. This CPU has 6 cores and 12 threads, making it excellent for gaming and productivity. The 5600gt is perfect for gaming on a budget and it pairs perfectly with GPU's like Nvidias RTX 4060 and 4060 ti. 

CPU Cooler: 
This wasn't too hard of a choice, the 5600gt only consumes 65w of power so the stock cooler it comes will will work just fine, and I was even able to overclock it to 4.65 GHz with this cooler.

MOBO:
I chose this Gigabyte motherboard because of its B550 chipset. This is the last-generation chipset for the AM4 platform so it can pair perfectly with any AM4 CPU. This Mobo allows for amazing upgradability potential in the future, so you won't need to be worried about your system getting too out of date.

RAM:
This was the best-looking ddr4 rgb ram kit I could find. It comes with a massive heatsink so you won't need to worry about it overheating. This RAM has a 32 GB capacity so you can dominate both gaming and productivity without breaking a sweat.

SSD: 
This was a clear choice for me. This was the best PCIE Gen 4 SD I could find. With the crazy read and write speeds of this SSD you will be able to load all your games before you can say "Why is this taking so long". And with 1 TB of storage, you will be able to store all the games you will ever need. 

GPU:
I chose the integrated graphics in this Ryzen CPU for 2 reasons. 1, since the graphics comes with the CPU I can lower the price of this PC by more than 400 dollars. 2, integrated graphics are able to run most titles in 1080p with decent framerates and you can upgrade to a dedicated GPU whenever you want!

Case:
I went with the Okinos Aqua 5 because the Aqua 3 wouldn't ship in time. At first, I was sad because I didn't get the case I wanted but when it arrived all I could say was "Wow." This case looks amazing, with a clean fish tank design, and 3 preinstalled RGB fans, I think that this is the best-looking case on the market.

PSU:
This is the best PSU I could fit into the budget. Rated tier B, This PSU won't explode on you! With 750 watts, this will be able to fit any upgrade you want. 

If you are questioning if you should buy this, I think that that's OK, buying a PC is a huge deal, and it is fine if you are a little indecisive. I think that it is best to do whatever you want to do with your money.
